  "texts": [
    "Future studies could use the abstract collections collected for this retrospective screening simulation to understand the impact of content-specific factors in the abstract collections while controlling for sample size and prevalence.",
    "These analyses may reveal features that affect the performance of learning algorithms and heuristic strategies in the educational psychology literature.",
    "Finally, given that the results on the performance of heuristic stopping criteria are highly dependent on dataset characteristics, it is advisable to extend the study to evaluate the effectiveness and generalizability of statistical stopping criteria, such as those proposed by Callaghan and Müller-Hansen (2020).",
    "This study examined various learning algorithms and evaluated the effectiveness of different heuristic stopping criteria in reducing the time and effort required for abstract screening in systematic reviews in educational psychology research.",
    "The findings indicated that active learning could expedite the screening process for education researchers by enabling them to identify relevant records faster than random screening."
